{"session_id":"3d62c6c7-1211-4864-a28c-9073abd54efd","transcript_path":"/Users/nat/.claude/projects/-Users-nat-Code-github-com-Soul-Brews-Studio-opensource-nat-brain-oracle/3d62c6c7-1211-4864-a28c-9073abd54efd.jsonl","cwd":"/Users/nat/Code/github.com/Soul-Brews-Studio/opensource-nat-brain-oracle","permission_mode":"plan","hook_event_name":"PreToolUse","tool_name":"Agent","tool_input":{"description":"Design /distill skill plan","prompt":"Design a `/distill` skill for the Oracle system. Here's the full context:\n\n## What Oracle Is\nAn \"external brain\" system for Nat Weerawan. It captures patterns, learnings, and philosophy across AI sessions. The brain data lives in ψ/ (psi) directories.\n\n## The Knowledge Flow\n```\nactive/context → logs → retrospectives → learnings → resonance\n(raw)           (snap)  (session)        (patterns)   (soul)\n```\n\n## The Problem\nRaw data is massive (hundreds of files). When sharing the brain or birthing new Oracles, there's too much noise. The rightward movement (compression) isn't automated.\n\n## User Requirements\n1. Multiple distillation runs - each time reads old distillations, adds new findings\n2. Date-time stamped like /trace (e.g., `ψ/memory/distillations/2026-03-02/1326_philosophy.md`)\n3. Metadata on each distillation: which model, why, what was input, what was extracted\n4. Each run finds NEW patterns, never repeats previous distillation content\n5. Goal: extract patterns of Nat Weerawan from Oracle data\n\n## Skill File Format\n```yaml\n---\ninstaller: oracle-skills-cli v2.0.5\norigin: Nat Weerawan's brain, digitized — how one human works with AI, captured as code — Soul Brews Studio\nname: distill\ndescription: v2.0.5 G-SKLL | [description]\n---\n```\n\n## Existing Patterns to Follow\n- `/trace`: timestamped files in `ψ/memory/traces/YYYY-MM-DD/HHMM_slug.md`\n- `/dig`: session mining, read-only\n- `/rrr`: retrospective creation\n\n## Resonance (Soul) File Characteristics\n- Lead with problem, not solution\n- Show raw data + interpretation side-by-side\n- Admit contradiction & limitation\n- Specific numbers (not \"many\")\n- Sources & traceable provenance\n- Journey arc (not static)\n- Frequency analysis instead of opinions\n- Vulnerability + data = depth\n- Thai for emotion, English for structure\n\n## Distillation Levels\n\n| Level | Input | Output | Purpose |\n|-------|-------|--------|---------|\n| L1: Compress | 20 retrospectives | 1 theme summary | Reduce volume |\n| L2: Extract | 50 learnings | 5 pattern files | Find patterns |\n| L3: Essence | All patterns | 1 resonance file | Synthesize |\n| L4: Soul | All resonance | 1 soul.md | Ultimate compression |\n\n## Modes\n- `/distill` — Default: smart mode, auto-detect what to distill\n- `/distill [topic]` — Focus on specific topic (e.g., \"philosophy\", \"work-patterns\")\n- `/distill --full` — Full brain distillation across all topics\n- `/distill --diff` — Show what's new since last distillation (read-only)\n\n## Key Design Decisions\n1. Output goes to `ψ/memory/distillations/YYYY-MM-DD/HHMM_topic.md`\n2. Each distillation file includes frontmatter: model, timestamp, input_sources, previous_distillation\n3. The skill reads previous distillations first, then only extracts NEW patterns\n4. Uses parallel Explore agents (haiku) for data gathering, main agent (opus) for actual distillation writing (like /rrr pattern)\n5. Log to Oracle MCP via oracle_learn after distillation\n\nDesign a concrete SKILL.md file structure with step-by-step instructions that Claude can follow. Include:\n- Step 0: Timestamp + paths\n- Step 1: Read previous distillations for this topic\n- Step 2: Gather raw data (parallel agents)\n- Step 3: Diff - identify what's new\n- Step 4: Main agent writes distillation\n- Step 5: Write file + log to Oracle\n\nMake it practical and executable, matching the trace/dig skill format.","subagent_type":"Plan","model":"sonnet"},"tool_use_id":"toolu_01L7vdi3a1Ei9roZuxofwwEF"}
